1. University Registration System
Case Study:
A university wants to register students using default, parameterized, and copy constructors.
Code:
class Student {
int roll;
String name, dept;
Student() {
roll = 0;
name = "Not Assigned";
dept = "NA";
}
Student(int r, String n, String d) {
roll = r;
name = n;
dept = d;
}
Student(Student s) {
roll = s.roll;
name = s.name;
dept = s.dept;
}
}

2. Bank Account Initialization
Case Study:
Demonstrate constructor overloading with default balance logic.
Code:
class BankAccount {
String name;
double balance;

BankAccount() {
balance = 1000;
}
BankAccount(String n, double b) {
name = n;
balance = b;
}
}

3. Employee ID Auto Generation
Case Study:
Use static variable and constructor for auto ID generation.
Code:
class Employee {
static int counter = 100;
int empId;
Employee() {
empId = counter++;
}
}

4. Immutable Student Record
Case Study:
Create immutable class using constructor.
Code:
final class Student {
private final int roll;
private final String name;
Student(int r, String n) {
roll = r;
name = n;
}
}

5. Constructor Chaining
Case Study:
Use this() to chain constructors.
Code:
class Student {
int roll;
String name;
Student() {
this(0, "NA");
}
Student(int r, String n) {
roll = r;
name = n;
}
}
